 body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."]},{"name":"Nicolò","meanings":["feminine form of   Nicholas ."]},{"name":"Niccolò","meanings":["feminine form of   Nicholas ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Nicola de Rigmaiden was born in 1280, in Preston, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, her father, John De Rigmaiden II, was 75 and her mother, Iola de Radcliffe, was 72. She married Roger de Brockholes. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died after 1319, in her hometown."},"et":{"1280–after 1319":"1280–pärast 1319","1280–1319":"1280–1319","1280–1311":"1280–1311","1312–1348":"1312–1348","1206–1305":"1206–1305","1208–Female":"1208–Surnud","1305":"1305","1206":"1206","1348":"1348","1224":"1224","1312":"1312","1311":"1311","after 1319":"pärast 1319","About 1312":"umbes 1312","1319":"1319","1280":"1280","1208":"1208","Preston, Lancashire, England":"Preston, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1280–after 1319":"1280–1319 jälkeen","1280–1319":"1280–1319","1280–1311":"1280–1311","1312–1348":"1312–1348","1206–1305":"1206–1305","1208–Female":"1208–Kuollut","1305":"1305","1206":"1206","1348":"1348","1224":"1224","1312":"1312","1311":"1311","after 1319":"1319 jälkeen","About 1312":"noin 1312","1319":"1319","1280":"1280","1208":"1208","Preston, Lancashire, England":"Preston, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1280–after 1319":"1280–après 1319","1280–1319":"1280–1319","1280–1311":"1280–1311","1312–1348":"1312–1348","1206–1305":"1206–1305","1208–Female":"1208–Décédée","1305":"1305","1206":"1206","1348":"1348","1224":"1224","1312":"